reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 3, 2024
reviews.reviewText: This printer works great with my HP All-In-One touch desktop computer. I didn’t need to print colors so this was perfect. It was pretty easy to set up. The print quality is crisp and clear. I don’t print a lot so I’m sure the printer cartridge will last quite a while. I purchased this as my other printer (that used ink from bottles) stopped working due to the ink drying up and gunking up the print jets. I quickly decided that I wasn’t going that route again, so while searching for a replacement printer, I found this one while it was on sale. I’m happy with this purchase!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 21, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars A printer that works
reviews.reviewText: If you do not need color. this is a home printer that works. I don't use a printer every day, but when I do, I want it to deliver without any resets or demands for new expensive ink(s). This HP LaserJet Pro prints cleanly, without tinkering or dried up ink tanks pr malfunctioning ink heads. This one is reliable and constant.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 5, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Good printer with not so good wifi.
reviews.reviewText: Wifi system is difficult to establish connection. Printer 10 feet from router and won't recognize it. Easy to hard wire so don't need wifi so the printer works very well without wireless connection.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 23, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great product. Easy to set up.
reviews.reviewText: We installed this as a second home printer. I LOVE the black and white laser.It is fast and cheap. This one even does automatic duplex printing to save paper.The B&W is fine for us. We ran through so many color cartridges over the years when my wife printed out recipes or craft ideas. The B&W is fine for us--and so much cheaper. The cartridges last us probably over a year.We have not tried the envelopes function. Easy connection via the HP setup process.Make sure to put the printer on the same WiFi as the laptops/smartphones/iPads in the house. We have a WiFi repeater that we use for better coverage--you have to make sure they are all on the same network.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 7, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars Nothing good about it
reviews.reviewText: Setup was an absolute nightmare. Like others have said, the Wifi couldn't find it when it was sitting near several other items that were picked up by the Wifi. I had to download a "problem solver" app to get it to work, that app screwed up my other printer, and now I can't print duplex with it. After weeks of wrangling with this printer I finally just plugged it into a network plug with a Cat cable and finally got it set up to use on the network. The first time I went to use it, it broke and can't pick up paper and thinks it's out of paper. Absolute waste of money. Total piece of garbage.
